# Corrected Response

Artificial intelligence is changing the software engineering profession by automating repetitive tasks, assisting with code generation, debugging, documentation, and testing. Many developers now use AI tools to improve productivity.

However, there is no reliable evidence that AI will eliminate the vast majority of software engineering jobs within the next five years. Instead, many experts expect software engineering roles to evolve, with developers increasingly working alongside AI systems.

Junior developers may face changing expectations as AI handles more routine work, but foundational programming skills, problem-solving, software design, security, and system architecture remain valuable. Universities continue to invest in computer science education while expanding AI-focused courses to prepare students for an evolving industry.

Rather than replacing software engineers entirely, AI is currently best understood as a powerful tool that changes how software is developed.

